AWS Central – Priority View
Priority 1 – Foundational / Immediate Platform Enablement

These are the most important items because they unblock multiple downstream asks and platform capabilities.

Serverless enablement and rollout
Cross-cloud Delta Sharing (AWS–Azure)
DR and HA support across AWS teams
Managed File Events
Automatic notifications for expiring personal access tokens / service principal expiry alerts
Attribute-Based Access Control (ABAC)
Integrated cost monitoring and Databricks billing/usage dashboard
Authentication login correction (EID to email format alignment)
OAuth token federation
Trigger jobs when source tables are updated
PrivateLink implementation
Databricks Apps enablement (dependent on serverless)
Why these are high priority

These items establish the platform foundation, strengthen governance, improve operational control, and support multiple future features such as advanced engineering workflows, integrations, and AI capabilities.

Priority 2 – Shared Engineering, Connectivity, and Operational Controls

These are the next set of important requirements needed to improve engineering productivity, integrations, and operational maturity.

Databricks SQL alerts
Alert enablement / correct email routing
Lakeflow support (requires serverless)
Databricks Zerobus feature
Apache Iceberg REST-compliant catalog setup on top of Unity Catalog
Lakehouse Connections in CICD for Oracle, Redshift, Salesforce, Snowflake, etc.
Enable Genie through pipeline
SharePoint connector
SFTP connector
GitHub connectivity / notebook source control integration
Data as a service
Secrets vault approach / secure secret management
Read-only access to all workspaces
Managed group / service principal access control for pools
Standardized auto-stop / auto-shutdown implementation
Marketplace enablement
Snowflake connection type support
External location support improvements
Enable file events in external locations
Dedicated VPC for Databricks
Why these are important

These requests help AWS Central support application onboarding, integrations, operational stability, platform standardization, and engineering automation.

Priority 3 – Strategic / Advanced Capability Enablement

These are strategic items that improve innovation, optimization, and long-term platform maturity.

Databricks Genie enablement
Data Quality Monitoring at scale with Agentic AI
Connect Genie spaces to Microsoft Copilot Studio
Dashboard and Genie spaces tagging
Agentic computing and MCP service enablement
Database Lakebase
Data lifecycle management for hot/cold storage, archival, and deletion
Model serving endpoint
Databricks usage dashboard enhancements
Bundle-based cost analysis support
Integration between AWS Central Databricks and GCS JupiterOne
Promote app config values from DEV → UAT → PROD
Support procedures / platform operational support improvements
Install R library on Databricks cluster
Enhance AWS Transfer Family–related user details screen
Why these are lower in execution priority

These items are important for maturity and innovation, but many of them depend on foundational platform controls, serverless readiness, networking, governance, and core operational features being in place first.
